# UX & Accessibility Enterprise Standards

## üåç Accessibility-First Design (WCAG 2.1 AA Compliance)

**Before creating any UI component, ensure:**

### 1. Keyboard Navigation
- **Tab order**: Logical and predictable navigation sequence
- **Focus indicators**: Visible focus states for all interactive elements
- **Keyboard shortcuts**: Standard keyboard interactions (Enter, Space, Arrow keys)
- **Skip links**: Navigation bypass for screen readers
- **Trapped focus**: Proper focus management in modals and dialogs

### 2. Screen Reader Support
- **Semantic HTML**: Use proper HTML elements for their intended purpose
- **ARIA labels**: Descriptive labels for complex interactions
- **Alt text**: Meaningful descriptions for images and media
- **Headings**: Proper heading hierarchy (h1, h2, h3...)
- **Form labels**: Clear association between labels and form controls

### 3. Visual Accessibility
- **Color contrast**: Minimum 4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text
- **Color independence**: Information not conveyed by color alone
- **Text size**: Scalable fonts, readable at 200% zoom
- **Visual hierarchy**: Clear content organization and relationships

## üé® User Experience Design Principles

### User-Centered Design Process
1. **User Research**: Understand actual user needs and contexts
2. **Persona Development**: Specific user archetypes, not generic assumptions
3. **Journey Mapping**: Current vs future state user workflows
4. **Usability Testing**: Validation with real users, including assistive technology users

### Inclusive Design Patterns
- **Progressive Enhancement**: Start with basic functionality, add enhancements
- **Responsive Design**: Mobile-first, works on all device sizes
- **Performance**: Fast loading, works on slow connections
- **Offline Support**: Graceful degradation when connectivity is poor

## üîç Accessibility Testing Requirements

### Manual Testing Checklist
- [ ] **Keyboard only**: Complete all tasks using only keyboard
- [ ] **Screen reader**: Test with NVDA, JAWS, or VoiceOver
- [ ] **High contrast**: Test in Windows High Contrast Mode
- [ ] **Zoom test**: Usable at 200% zoom without horizontal scrolling
- [ ] **Color blindness**: Test with color blindness simulators
- [ ] **Reduced motion**: Respect prefers-reduced-motion settings

### Automated Testing Tools
- **axe-core**: Integrate accessibility testing into CI/CD
- **Wave**: Browser extension for accessibility evaluation
- **Lighthouse**: Accessibility audit in Chrome DevTools
- **Pa11y**: Command-line accessibility testing

